Tensor rank

Tensor rank
Tensor rank

The smallest number of rank-one tensors that generate is called the tensor rank, denoted . This is the same as the smallest number of components in an exact CP decomposition.

Properties
  • The components of the best rank- approximation may not be solved for sequentially (unlike matrix case).
  • The best rank- approximation may not exits.

A tensor is degenerate is it may be approximated arbitrary well by a factorization of lower rank.

For instance, for a rank-three tensor there can be a sequence of rank-two tensors that provide increasingly better estimates. As the set of rank-two tensors is open they may converge to of rank other than two.

Border rank is defined as the minimum number of rank-one tensors that are sufficient to approximate the given tensor with arbitrarily small nonzero error:
